The '''Green Party of Egypt''' (''Hizb Al-khodr'') is a [[Green party|Green political party]] in [[Egypt]]. The party presses for protection and promotion of the ecological system and optimal use of resources. It also calls for drawing up solutions to the problems of poverty, underdevelopment and challenges the disadvantages of globalism and capitalism, following the global trend of many traditional green parties now embracing [[Ecosocialism]].<ref name="EgyptEcosocialsts">{{cite web |url=http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&sl=auto&tl=en&u=http://www.egyptiangreens.com/docs/general/index.php%3Feh%3Dnewhit%26subjectid%3D27843%26subcategoryid%3D262%26categoryid%3D36&rurl=translate.google.com&twu=1&usg=ALkJrhiH7_voTxcoiGmgaTRwnducMBTdUw |title=Another world is possible, and his name is eco-socialism |author=Egyptian Green Party }}</ref>
Egyptian Greens also oppose the [[Nuclear proliferation|proliferation of Nuclear Weapons]], strongly objecting to President [[Hosni Mubarak]]'s [[Nuclear Power]] proposals.<ref name="NuclearTrap">{{cite web |url=http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&sl=auto&tl=en&u=http://www.egyptiangreens.com/docs/general/index.php%3Feh%3Dnewhit%26subjectid%3D18491%26subcategoryid%3D259%26categoryid%3D36&rurl=translate.google.com&twu=1&usg=ALkJrhgIj4QAA5V2-0yAJ7umc83pnmPyXA |title=Green Party Rejects Egypt's Nuclear Project |author=Egyptian Green Party }}</ref><ref name="MubNuclear">{{cite web |url= http://www.larouchepub.com/other/2006/3341egypt_nuclear.html |title=Mubarak Says: "Let's Go Nulclear!" |author=Executive Intelligence Review }}</ref>
It was founded by former diplomat [[Hassan Ragab]] in 1990, experienced a hiatus in 1995, and was revived in 1998.
The president of the Green Party, Dr. [[Abdul Moneim Al-A'sar|Abdel Munem Ali Ali Al Aasar]], serves in the [[Shura Council]] and is probably the only Green Party member in the [[Parliament of Egypt]].
After the [[2011 Egyptian revolution|25th of January revolution in Egypt]] the party is reforming to effectively and positively contribute in a democratic atmosphere, the party is adopting several issues especially concerning sustainable development and environmental issues in Egypt. The party is a member of the [[Global Greens]] and the African Greens
== Platform == The party platform calls for: * Promotion of the ecological system. * Rendering [[social justice]] to the citizens. * Striking a balance between incomes and prices. * Resorting to religion as a main guideline to solving daily problems. * Adoption of Free Market policies as Egypt's main economic system.
